SUMMARY—Provides for the establishment of a program by a
county or city to provide certain housing facilities to
assist persons experiencing homelessness.
(BDR 20-863)
FISCAL NOTE: Effect on Local Government: No.
Effect on the State: No.
~
EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to housing; authorizing counties and cities to
establish a program to provide certain housing facilities to
assist persons experiencing homelessness; and providing
other matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law sets forth various powers and duties of counties and cities.
2 (Chapters 244 and 268 of NRS) Sections 1 and 2 of this bill authorize a board of
3 county commissioners and each city council or other governing body of an
4 incorporated city to establish a program to provide housing for persons
5 experiencing homelessness. Sections 1 and 2 require such a program to provide:
6 (1) a housing facility for persons experiencing homelessness that consists of certain
7 individual units and a community kitchen; and (2) supportive services for the
8 persons experiencing homelessness who reside in the facility.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 244 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto a new section to read as follows:
3 1. A board of county commissioners may create a program to
4 provide housing for persons experiencing homelessness.
5 2. Except as otherwise provided in subsection 3, the program
6 must provide:
